In a speech in Pittsburgh, President Joe Biden highlighted the importance of infrastructure investment and the impact it can have on communities. He discussed the collapse of the Fern Hollow Bridge and how it highlighted the need for improved infrastructure. The President emphasized the significance of the recently passed Bipartisan Infrastructure Law, which will provide funding for roads, bridges, railways, ports, airports, and other infrastructure projects. He mentioned specific projects in Pennsylvania, such as the repair of the Fern Hollow Bridge and the replacement and expansion of the Montgomery Locks and Dam. President Biden also highlighted investments in clean energy, high-speed internet access, and the replacement of lead pipes. He emphasized that these projects will create good-paying jobs and help rebuild the middle class. The President expressed optimism about America's future and the potential for continued progress through working together.